<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Ending With -IST — Scrabble Suffix Scoring Guide</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -IST suffix creates person nouns — the practitioner, believer, or specialist form of a concept. PHYSICIST, CYCLIST, OPTIMIST — these words are Scrabble gold because they're 7-9 letters naturally, landing them squarely in bingo territory. At 3 base points (I1+S1+T1) the suffix is cheap to add but builds long, high-scoring words.</p>

<p>Combined with the -ISM pattern, learning -IST words gives you a powerful two-suffix vocabulary system from a single set of roots.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -IST Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">I(1)+S(1)+T(1) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">250+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -IST words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4–10</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>I, S, and T are all common tiles (9 Is, 4 Ss, 6 Ts in the bag). You'll often have these together. The power of -IST is its natural word length — most valid forms are 7+ letters, qualifying for the 50-point bingo bonus. Combined with high-value roots containing PH, Y, X, or K, -IST words routinely score 15-20+ points before premium squares.</p>

