<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Double with -ISM:</span> Every -IST you know gives you a free -ISM word too. OPTIMIST→OPTIMISM, CYCLIST→CYCLISM (not valid — check each). Learning valid pairs doubles your bingo arsenal.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">S-hook everything:</span> Nearly every -IST word takes an S (PHYSICISTS, CYCLISTS, CHEMISTS). If an opponent plays an -IST word, you can hook S for free parallel scoring.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target PH and CH roots:</span> The highest -IST words use PH (PHYSICIST=19) or CH (CHEMIST=14). These digraphs add 7 or 6 points to any root — keep them together when you have I+S+T available.</p>
  </div>
</div>

